INDUSTRIAL APPLICABILITY





The peptidic compounds of the present invention having CXCR4 antagonistic activity can inhibit the interaction of CXCR4 and CXCL12/SDF-1α, and accordingly, can inhibit the migrating reaction of cancerous cells of cancers impressing CXCR4, for example, oral cancer, throat cancer, lip cancer, lingual cancer, gingival cancer, nasopharyngeal cancer, esophageal cancer, gastric cancer, small intestinal cancer, large intestinal cancer including colorectal cancer, liver cancer, gallbladder cancer, pancreatic cancer, nasal cancer, lung cancer, bone cancer, soft tissue cancer, skin cancer, melanoma, breast cancer, uterine cancer, ovarian cancer, prostate cancer, testicular cancer, penile cancer, bladder cancer, kidney cancer, brain cancer, thyroid cancer, lymphoma, leukemia, etc., and are useful as drugs for the prevention and/or therapy of these cancers. Also, the peptidic compounds of the present invention can inhibit the migrating reaction of immunocytes induced by CXCL12/SDF-1α and are useful as drugs for the prevention and/or therapy of chronic rheumatoid arthritis.
